RelatedSentence: Nebraska 's Director of Economic Development and Commissioner of Labor Catherine Lang has resigned to pursue a job in the private sector .
Nebraska 's economic development director and state labor commissioner has resigned to take a private sector job .
Catherine Lang will leave state government next month after more than three decades of service .
Gov. Dave Heineman announced her resignation on Monday .
She was appointed Commissioner of Labor in August 2008 , after serving as deputy tax commissioner .
Both agencies have worked on efforts to find jobs for veterans .
During Lang 's tenure , the Department of Economic Development opened a trade office in China .
Lang earned her bachelor 's and law degrees from the University of Nebraska - Lincoln .
